## Copy this file to `local.properties` in the repo root and set `sdk.dir`.
## When `sdk.dir` (or ANDROID_HOME / ANDROID_SDK_ROOT) is set, Gradle will include `:android-app`.
## Example (Windows, Android Studio SDK):
# sdk.dir=C\:\\Users\\YOU\\AppData\\Local\\Android\\Sdk
##
## This repo can also use a workspace-local SDK under `.android-sdk/` (see cmdline-tools there).
## Install packages once (PowerShell), then `.\gradlew.bat :android-app:assembleDebug`:
##   $r="C:\path\to\repo\.android-sdk"
##   & "$r\cmdline-tools\latest\bin\sdkmanager.bat" --sdk_root=$r "platform-tools" "platforms;android-34" "build-tools;34.0.0"
##
## Debug APK output: android-app\build\outputs\apk\debug\android-app-debug.apk
##
## Root `gradle.properties` enables AndroidX (required for Material/Room). `security-crypto` uses 1.1.0-alpha06 for MasterKey API.
